main event: A civilian reported a sighting of a starlike object larger than a star in Centerville, Ohio on February 17, 1966.
interesting points: The object appeared stationary and was observed for a duration of 22 minutes,The object was seen in the East at approximately 75 degrees azimuth and 10 degrees elevation,The object was about 45 degrees off from Venus's position,The description included the appearance of the object as whirling, and there was a dog barking during the observation,The report concludes with an identification of the object as likely being Venus.
sighted object: starlike object larger than a star
